    <abstract id="Abs1">
      <sec>
        <title>Background</title>
        <p id="Par1">RNA editing is a widespread co-/post-transcriptional mechanism that alters primary RNA sequences through the modification of specific nucleotides and it can increase both the transcriptome and proteome diversity. The automatic detection of RNA-editing from RNA-seq data is computational intensive and limited to small data sets, thus preventing a reliable genome-wide characterisation of such process.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec>
        <title>Results</title>
        <p id="Par2">In this work we introduce HPC-REDItools, an upgraded tool for accurate RNA-editing events discovery from large dataset repositories. Availability: <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/BioinfoUNIBA/REDItools2">https://github.com/BioinfoUNIBA/REDItools2</ext-link>.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec>
        <title>Conclusions</title>
        <p id="Par3">HPC-REDItools is dramatically faster than the previous version, REDItools, enabling big-data analysis by means of a MPI-based implementation and scaling almost linearly with the number of available cores.</p>
      </sec>
    </abstract>
